title: Google\Cloud\Talent\V4beta1\JobApplication
name: JobApplication
description:
Resource that represents a job application record of a candidate.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.talent.v4beta1.JobApplication

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

methods.name: __construct
methods.description: Constructor.

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.job
params.description: Optional. The information of job which the candidate applied for. If [Job.name][google.cloud.talent.v4beta1.Job.name] is provided, the corresponding [Job][google.cloud.talent.v4beta1.Job] must be created. Otherwise, only [Job.requisition_id][google.cloud.talent.v4beta1.Job.requisition_id], [Job.title][google.cloud.talent.v4beta1.Job.title], [Job.description][google.cloud.talent.v4beta1.Job.description] and [Job.addresses][google.cloud.talent.v4beta1.Job.addresses] provided here are persisted in the application. No [Job][google.cloud.talent.v4beta1.Job] entity is created in this case.

params.name: data.application_id
params.description: Optional. The job application id. Number of characters allowed is 100.

params.name: data.application_date
params.description: Optional. The application date.

params.name: data.last_stage
params.description: Optional. The last stage the candidate reached in the application progress. For example, "new", "phone screen", "interview".

params.name: data.state
params.description: Optional. The application state.

params.name: data.average_interview_score
params.description: Optional. The average interview score.

params.name: data.interview_score_scale_id
params.description: Optional. The scale id of the interview score. Number of characters allowed is 100.

params.name: data.number_of_interviews
params.description: Optional. The number of interviews.

params.name: data.is_employee_referred
params.description: Optional. If the candidate is referred by a employee.

params.name: data.update_time
params.description: Optional. The last update timestamp.

params.name: data.outcome_reason
params.description: Optional. The outcome reason for the job application. Number of characters allowed is 100.

params.name: data.outcome_positiveness
params.description: Optional. Outcome positiveness shows how positive the outcome is. Currently only -1, 0 and 1 are accepted, where -1 means not positive, 0 means neutral and 1 means positive. An error is thrown if other value is set.

params.name: data.is_match
params.description: Output only. Indicates whether this job application is a match to application related filters. This value is only applicable in profile search response.

params.name: data.job_title_snippet
params.description: Output only. Job title snippet shows how the job title is related to a search query. It's empty if the job title isn't related to the search query.
